  "title": "Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p>At Rainbow Centre, we believe in a world where persons with disabilities are empowered and thriving in inclusive communities. Our team of passionate social workers supports children and youth with disabilities and their families in leading meaningful lives—where they are safe, connected, healthy, and heard.</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>The Administration Operations Executive is responsible for ensuring the smooth and effective daily operations of RC’s services. The role provides reliable administrative, data, and operational support to service leaders and teams, enabling them to focus on high-quality service delivery to clients and families. This role supports a broad range of administrative and operational functions, including financial and staff administration, client records management, procurement support, data integrity, reporting, and customer service.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>A good diploma or tertiary qualification in Business Administration, Linguistics, Economics or other relevant field</p></li><li><p>Experience in business administration, finance, procurement or customer service will be an advantage</p></li><li><p>Experience with project management software (e.g., Asana, Trello, Jira) and CRM systems is a plus</p></li></ul><p><strong>Service is at the heart of RC’s purpose and we seek to serve our clients with respect, dedication and compassion, understanding that we are entrusted by society to serve with excellence and the highest ethical standards. Join us if you share our passion and values.</strong><br />\n\n</p>",
